  "note": "All 82 Mississippi counties are documented; sheriffs were elected Nov 7, 2023 to four-year terms beginning January 2024, with several mid-term changes since: Tallahatchie (William Brewer resigned amid federal charges, Jimmy Fly appointed), Noxubee (Tommy Roby retired 2025, Tedrick Liddell won a special election), Hancock (Ricky Adam resigned Jan 2026, Johnny Alison appointed interim), and after the October 2025 FBI Delta drug-sting indictments Humphreys (Bruce Williams stepped aside, Mickey Foxworth interim) and Washington (Milton Gaston remains the elected sheriff of record while chief deputy Billy Barber runs the office)."
